eNCA's Masego Rahlaga spoke to a company that supplies some 190 countries with needles and syringes. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The COVID-19 pandemic has resulted in high demand for medical supplies worldwide. Mass vaccine rollouts mean countries need more needles and syringes than ever before. READ: COVID-19 pandemic: Mortuaries struggle to keep up with demand Prices have increased - and in South Africa, they have doubled. The deadly virus is wreaking havoc as the health systems of many countries have plunged into chaos. While countries race to achieve herd immunity, the rollout of vaccines has increased, meaning more pressure on companies supplying needles and syringes. eNCA's Masego Rahlaga spoke to a company that supplies some 190 countries.